spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:script: Enable('COEF_SYMM', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Enumerated'));\ Enable('SYSTOLIC', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Enumerated'));\ Enable('CLOCK_RATE', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Folded'));\ Enable('SAMPLEID', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Folded'));\ Enable('ID_WIDTH', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Folded'));\ Enable('DATA_RAM', Or(Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Folded'), And(Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Decimated'), Or(Eq('FAMILY', '19'), Eq('FAMILY', '24'), Eq('FAMILY', '25')), Gt('M', '2'))));\ Enable('COEF_RAM', Or(Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Folded'), And(Gt('L', '2'), Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Interpolated')), And(Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Decimated'), Gt('M', '2'))));\ Enable('L', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Interpolated'));\ Enable('SAMPLE_RATE', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Folded'));\ Enable('INP_REG', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Enumerated'));\ Enable('M', Eq('CFG_ARCH', 'Decimated'));\ Enable('URAM_MAXDEPTH', And(Or(Eq('FPGA_FAMILY', '19'), Eq('FPGA_FAMILY', '24'), Eq('FPGA_FAMILY', '25')), Neq('CFG_ARCH', 'Enumerated')));\

spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: Finite Impulse Response (FIR) filter utilizing hard multiplier-accumulator (MAC) blocks. Choose between single rate Fully Enumerated, single rate Folded and multi-rate Polyphase interpolation or decimation FIR filter implementations. The core supports filters with constant coefficients, constant multiple coefficient sets, or run-time reloadable coefficients. Number of filter taps ranges from 2 to 1024 depending on the filter type, and number of available MAC. The filter accepts signed data and coefficients of up to 18 bits wide, and unsigned data/coefficients of up to 17 bits.
